[1;31;4m                      Cron Jobs (cronie Package)                      [0;0m
[0;0m
[0;33msudo crontab -l[1;30m - [0;34mList all cron jobs[0;0m
[0;33msudo -E crontab -e[1;30m - [0;34mEdit the crontab file preserving editor environment variables[0;0m
[0;0m
[0;32mEach line has five time-and-date fields followed by a command and new line.[0;0m
[0;32mThe fields are separated by spaces (fields cannot contain spaces).[0;0m
[0;32mThe five time-and-date fields are as follows:[0;0m
[0;0m
[0;31m minute (0-59)[0;0m
[0;31m |  [0;33mhour (0-23, 0 = midnight)[0;0m
[0;31m |  [0;33m|  [0;32mday (1-31)[0;0m
[0;31m |  [0;33m|  [0;32m|  [0;34mmonth (1-12)[0;0m
[0;31m |  [0;33m|  [0;32m|  [0;34m|  [0;35mweekday (0-6, 0 = Sunday)[0;0m
[0;31m |  [0;33m|  [0;32m|  [0;34m|  [0;35m|  [0;0mscript file or executable[0;0m
[0;31m V  [0;33mV  [0;32mV  [0;34mV  [0;35mV  [0;0mV
[0;31m 00 [0;33m00 [0;32m01 [0;34m*  [0;35m*  [0;0m/directories/script.sh
[0;0m
[0;32mThe cron log is found here: [0;33mnano /var/log/cron[0;0m
[0;32mMore info here: [0;36mhttps://help.ubuntu.com/community/CronHowto[0;0m
[0;0m
[0;32mAnacron directory locations:[0;0m
[0;33m/etc/cron.d[0;0m
[0;33m/etc/cron.daily[0;0m
[0;33m/etc/cron.hourly[0;0m
[0;33m/etc/cron.weekly[0;0m
[0;33m/etc/cron.monthly[0;0m
